    {
      "index": 4,
      "type": "content",
      "title": "第 2 页",
      "audio": "assets/ppt/audio/ppt_2.mp3",
      "subtitles": [
        {
          "at": 0.1,
          "text": "In Book 1, we learned how to use “给” as a verb, which means \"to give\" "
        },
        {
          "at": 6,
          "text": "for example, \"请给我一杯牛奶\""
        },
        {
          "at": 10,
          "text": "Today, we are going to learn how to use “给” as a preposition."
        },
        {
          "at": 15,
          "text": "As a preposition, “给” is used to introduce the recipient or the beneficiary of an action."
        },
        {
          "at": 24,
          "text": "It is equivalent to the English words \"to\" or \"for\". The basic sentence structure is:"
        },
        {
          "at": 31,
          "text": "Subject + 给 + Recipient + Verb + Others"
        },
        {
          "at": 39,
          "text": "Here are some examples: 给妹妹打电话；医生正在给病人看病"
        },
        {
          "at": 47,
          "text": "Hope this explanation helps!"
        }
      ],
